[
  {
    "startTime": 0.0,
    "endTime": 2.74,
    "text": "Hey guys, it's Shane from English Understood here."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 2.74,
    "endTime": 9.76,
    "text": "If you listen to native speakers, you will hear that most of the time, they use contractions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 9.76,
    "endTime": 11.76,
    "text": "What is a contraction?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 11.76,
    "endTime": 17.919,
    "text": "Well, a contraction is a word that is shorter than the original word or words."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 18.4,
    "endTime": 21.04,
    "text": "Let me tell you five common examples."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 21.76,
    "endTime": 23.66,
    "text": "I have becomes:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 23.84,
    "endTime": 26.1,
    "text": "'I've.' 'I've.'"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 26.56,
    "endTime": 28.4,
    "text": "He is becomes:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 28.4,
    "endTime": 30.9,
    "text": "'He's.' 'He's.'"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 31.22,
    "endTime": 32.9,
    "text": "It is becomes:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 33.16,
    "endTime": 35.559,
    "text": "'It's.' 'It's.'"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 35.88,
    "endTime": 38.06,
    "text": "They are becomes:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 38.4,
    "endTime": 40.68,
    "text": "'They're.' 'They're.'"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 40.94,
    "endTime": 43.36,
    "text": "And they have becomes:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 43.64,
    "endTime": 46.12,
    "text": "'They've.' 'They've.'"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 46.34,
    "endTime": 48.120000000000005,
    "text": "Listen to this example."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 48.52,
    "endTime": 54.42,
    "text": "I have been going to the park a lot because it is where I exercise."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 55.04,
    "endTime": 56.66,
    "text": "Now, listen to this example."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.08,
    "endTime": 61.099999999999994,
    "text": "I've been going to the park a lot because it's where I exercise."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 61.1,
    "endTime": 64.4,
    "text": "Which one do you think sounds more like a native speaker?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 64.72,
    "endTime": 66.22,
    "text": "The second one, right?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 66.22,
    "endTime": 68.6,
    "text": "Because we used two contractions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.6,
    "endTime": 72.1,
    "text": "We said 'I've', and we said 'it's'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 72.36,
    "endTime": 76.2,
    "text": "So when you're speaking English, try and use more contractions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 76.2,
    "endTime": 80.36,
    "text": "This will make you sound more like a native speaker."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 80.36,
    "endTime": 89.2,
    "text": "But, please note that when speaking or writing quite formally, it's better to NOT use contractions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.2,
    "endTime": 92.9,
    "text": "But in everyday situations, it's fine to use contractions."
  }
]